}</h1>\n    <p>{post.body}</p>\n    <h2>Comments</h2>\n    {comments.map(comment =>\n      <EnhancedComment key={comment.id} comment={comment} />\n    )}\n  </article>\n)\n\nconst enhance = withObservables(['post'], ({ post }) => ({\n  post: post.observe(),\n  comments: post.comments.observe()\n}))\n\nconst EnhancedPost = enhance(Post)\n```\n\n**➡️ Learn more:** [Connecting WatermelonDB to Components](https://nozbe.github.io/WatermelonDB/Components.html)\n\n## Installation\n\n```bash\nyarn add @nozbe/with-observables\n```\n\nAnd then to use:\n\n```js\nimport withObservables from '@nozbe/with-observables'\n```\n\n## Usage\n\n```js\nwithObservables(triggerProps, getObservables)\n\n// Injects new props to a component with values from the passed Observables\n//\n// Every time one of the `triggerProps` changes, `getObservables()` is called\n// and the returned Observables are subscribed to.\n//\n// Every time one of the Observables emits a new value, the matching inner prop is updated.\n//\n// You can return multiple Observables in the function. You can also return arbitrary objects that have\n// an `observe()` function that returns an Observable.\n//\n// The inner component will not render until all supplied Observables return their first values.\n// If `triggerProps` change, renders will also be paused until the new Observables emit first values.\n//\n// If you only want to subscribe to Observables once (the Observables don't depend on outer props),\n// pass `null` to `triggerProps`.\n//\n// Example use:\n//   withObservables(['task'], ({ task }) => ({\n//     task: task,\n//     comments: task.comments.observe()\n//   }))\n```\n\n## Typescript\n\nThe TypeScript bindings expose a helper type, `ObservablifyProps<Props, ObservableKeys, ObservableConvertibleKeys>` which can make it easier to wrap components without duplicating interfaces:\n```ts\ninterface Props {\n  post: Post;\n  author: Author;\n  someOtherProp: boolean;\n  anotherProp: number;\n}\n\nconst PostRenderer: React.FC<Props> = (props) => ( ... );\n\ntype InputProps = ObservablifyProps<Props, \"author\", \"post\">\nconst enhance = withObservables([\"post\", \"author\"], ({ post }: InputProps) => ({\n  post,\n  author: author.observe()\n});\n\nexport default enhance(PostRenderer);\n```\n\n## Author and license\n\n**withObservables** was created by [@Nozbe](https://github.com/Nozbe) for [WatermelonDB](https://github.com/Nozbe/WatermelonDB).\n\nwithObservables is available under the MIT license. See the [LICENSE](./LICENSE) file for more info.\n","gitHead":"9b0426bf98e984811b888daaa475fbf9824c3a19","scripts":{"flow":"flow check","test":"jest --config=./jest.config.js --forceExit --detectOpenHandles --no-cache","build":"rollup -c","eslint":"eslint ./src -c ./.eslintrc.yml --cache --cache-location ./.cache/.eslintcache","ci:check":"concurrently 'yarn test' 'yarn eslint' 'yarn flow' --kill-others-on-fail"},"_npmUser":{"name":"radex","email":"this.is@radex.io"},"repository":{"url":"git+https://github.com/Nozbe/withObservables.git","type":"git"},"_npmVersion":"6.7.0","description":"<a href=\"https://opensource.org/licenses/MIT\">     <img src=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/License-MIT-blue.svg\" alt=\"MIT License\">   </a>","directories":{},"_nodeVersion":"11.10.1","dependencies":{"rxjs":"^6.4.0","hoist-non-react-statics":"^3.3.0"},"publishConfig":{"access":"public"},"_hasShrinkwrap":false,"readmeFilename":"README.md","devDependencies":{"jest":"^24.5.0","eslint":"^6.4.0","rollup":"^1.23.0","flow-bin":"^0.109.0","@babel/cli":"^7.2.3","babel-core":"^7.0.0-0","babel-jest":"^24.5.0","rollup-cli":"^1.0.9","@babel/core":"^7.3.4","babel-eslint":"10.0.3","concurrently":"^4.1.0","@babel/runtime":"^7.3.4","rollup-plugin-flow":"^1.1.1","eslint-plugin-react":"^7.12.4","rollup-plugin-babel":"^4.3.2","eslint-config-airbnb":"^17.1.0","eslint-plugin-import":"^2.17.2","rollup-plugin-replace":"^2.0.0","eslint-config-prettier":"^6.0.0","eslint-plugin-flowtype":"^4.2.0","eslint-plugin-jsx-a11y":"^